com.viaoa.html

Class OARadio

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.viaoa.html.OAHtmlComponent
      • com.viaoa.html.OARadio
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class OARadio
extends OAHtmlComponent
        [Java Code]
    OARadio rad;
    rad = new OARadio(hubJob,"hourly",true);
    form.add("radHourly",rad);
    rad = new OARadio(hubJob,"salary",false);
    form.add("radSalary",rad);
    ....
    [HTML Code]
    <input type="radio" name="radGroupName" value="<%=form.getRadio("radHourly").getValue()%>">
    <input type="radio" name="radGroupName" value="<%=form.getRadio("radSalary").getValue()%>">
    output =>
    <input type="radio" name="radType" value="Sample" checked vav="">
    NOTE: the HTML tag param "name" needs to be the same for all radio buttons in same group
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • OARadio

        public OARadio(com.viaoa.hub.Hub hub,
               com.viaoa.hub.Hub hubMasterList,
               String propertyPath,
               String masterPropertyPath)
        Create group of Radio buttons used to select a value from a list.
        Parameters:
        hubMasterList - hub with list of all objects
        hub - of selected objects - (this should be a detail hub)
        propertyPath - name to display with checkbox
        masterPropertyPath - name of property to use as label Note: can only be used by getHtml()
